16. prosequar: ‘ Ι will attend you.’ The external evidence is fairly divided between this word and ‘ persequarz’ ‘I will follow to the end.’ It is a common point of variation in MSS. On intemal grounds we may prefer ‘ prosequar,' the usual word for compli- mentary attendance, as giving a softer tone to the preceding word. The point is the unconseiousness of the interlo- cutor, not his brutality. ‘Persequar' would leave less room for the answer ‘ nil opus est te circumagi.'
